In 3 quart saucepan melt butter. Add garlic. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until golden. Add chicken pieces. Cook chicken until no longer pink in center. Add chicken broth, Simply Potatoes(R), cauliflower and mushrooms; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. In small bowl stir together milk and flour until mixture is a thick paste. Slowly stir flour mixture into soup. Cook until soup is thickened. Add coconut milk and curry powder. Cook until heated through.